=================================================================================================================================================
IRIO EPICS Device Support description:
=================================================================================================================================================
The IRIO EPICS Device Support main goal is the integration of advanced data acquisition applications in EPICS. It allows the users to develop
EPICS IOCs (using IRIO Library) to acquire data using NI RIO Hardware (cRIO and FlexRIO).This device support has been implemented using
asynDriver.
This device support implements different data acquisition profiles allowing direct I/O Data Acquisition, DMA Data Acquisition, and DMA Image
Acquisition, using cRIO and FlexRIO platforms. The resources implemented in the FPGA design can be controlled from EPICS using PVs based on the 
asyn interfaces (asynlnt32, asynOctet, asynFloat64, asynFloat32Array, asynlnt8Array, etc). 

In the following website, users can find all info needed about IRIO Technology.

Website: http://www.i2a2.upm.es/idi/instrumentacion-aplicada/sistemas-de-adquisicion-de-datos-avanzados-2/irio-technology/



=================================================================================================================================================
How to install IRIO Software Tools:
=================================================================================================================================================
In the following website, users can find all info needed about how to install next software packages in a ScientificLinux distribution.
-NI-RIO Linux Driver 
-EPICS Base
-SynApps (Busy, Sscan, Autosave and Calc)
-IRIO Library
-IRIO EPICS Device Support

WebSite: http://www.i2a2.upm.es/idi/instrumentacion-aplicada/sistemas-de-adquisicion-de-datos-avanzados-2/irio-software-tools-installation/



